// jul18d crash_000000's cross-kernel twin: same result seam through
// `emit_lambda_call_node` instead of the collection hook — g's
// kernel returns a raw array box per its own return ABI, the g()
// callsite node's type widened to f's param union, and the raw box
// pointer rode into f as a Value payload. Covered by the same
// `widen_result_to_value` fix (this shape pins the lambda-call path;
// 04 pins the collection-inline path).
{let g = || [i64:1]; let f = |v: [null, Array<i64>]| v; f(g())}
